cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper uses computational linguistics tools to explore and analyze a dataset of multilingual affective visual concepts. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper deals with visual emotion perception and uses a large dataset of Flickr images. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper focuses on analyzing and clustering multilingual visual concepts. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper uses word embeddings to represent visual concepts and evaluates them based on visual semantic relatedness. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper uses clustering schemes and novel evaluation metrics to group and analyze the multilingual visual concepts.
